<h2> </h2>
<h2>A Community of Student Artists Proudly Serving Grades 6 through 12</h2>
<p>Beacon Charter Schools, located in historic Monument Square in Woonsocket, Rhode Island, currently serves 375 student artists from nineteen cities and towns across Rhode Island.</p>
<p>Beacon Charter High School for the Arts opened in 2003 to <strong>B</strong>ring <strong>E</strong>ducational <strong>A</strong>lternatives to the <strong>C</strong>ommunity through <strong>O</strong>ccupational <strong>N</strong>urturing.  The school has a rich, decade and a half history of academic and artistic excellence</p>
<p>Founders Academy, Beacon’s middle school program, opened in 2015 to focus on strengthening students’ core academic skills while introducing them to Beacon’s three cornerstone arts programs.  Upon completion of grade 8 at Founders, students are promoted to grade 9 at Beacon.</p>
<p>Admission to all grades is made through blind lottery, held each year on March 1st.  Families are highly encouraged to apply in grade 6 to ensure the best possible chances of admission to our schools.</p>


